<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWinkler1980">Winkler, Gershon (1980). <i>The Golem of Prague: A New Adaptation of the Documented Stories of the Golem of Prague</i>. New York: Judaica Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0910818258" class="internal">ISBN 0-9108-1825-8</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Golem+of+Prague%3A+A+New+Adaptation+of+the+Documented+Stories+of+the+Golem+of+Prague&amp;rft.aulast=Winkler&amp;rft.aufirst=Gershon&amp;rft.au=Winkler%2C+Gershon&amp;rft.date=1980&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Judaica+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-9108-1825-8&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Golem"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGoldsmith1981">Goldsmith, Arnold L. (1981). <i>The Golem Remembered 1909-1980: Variations of a Jewish Legend</i>. Detroit: Wayne State University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0814316832" class="internal">ISBN 0-8143-16832</a>-8.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Golem+Remembered+1909-1980%3A+Variations+of+a+Jewish+Legend&amp;rft.aulast=Goldsmith&amp;rft.aufirst=Arnold+L.&amp;rft.au=Goldsmith%2C+Arnold+L.&amp;rft.date=1981&amp;rft.place=Detroit&amp;rft.pub=Wayne+State+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-8143-16832-8&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Golem"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFIdel1990">Idel, Mosche (1990). <i>Golem: Jewish Magical and Mystical Traditions on the Artificial Anthropoid</i>. Albany (NY): State University of New York Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/079140160X" class="internal">ISBN 0-7914-0160-X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Golem%3A+Jewish+Magical+and+Mystical+Traditions+on+the+Artificial+Anthropoid&amp;rft.aulast=Idel&amp;rft.aufirst=Mosche&amp;rft.au=Idel%2C+Mosche&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft.place=Albany+%28NY%29&amp;rft.pub=State+University+of+New+York+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-7914-0160-X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Golem"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
